@imzhenyu BTW, in the above example garbage collection happens only **after** the batch ends. Nothing will be garbage collected before then. So as long as you add an object to the return list, you can safely use that object elsewhere as soon as it is created as you know it won't be garbage collected during or after the batch ends (no need to wait for `return` -- probably need to change the name again).

In the above example, say you do a lot of stuff after creating `z`. You can still use `z` safely before the batch ends, as none of the objects will be garbage collected before then. 

Wouldn't this be enough for your cases?
